        <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇧🇫 Burkina Faso junta foiled a coup attempt
</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
Burkina Faso’s military junta claims to have <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-04-2025-h1-1-uncovered-a-coup-attempt?source=website" target="_blank">uncovered a coup attempt</a> aimed at destabilizing the country. According to the junta, the alleged plot involved an attack on the presidency, orchestrated by individuals in Ivory Coast, including two former military officers. The country’s intelligence service says the plan included soldiers recruited by Burkina Faso’s “external enemies.”
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
           Junta leader Ibrahim Traoré has accused the Ivory Coast of supporting efforts to undermine his government, mainly through domestic opposition groups. Since seizing power in 2022, his regime has intensified crackdowns on dissent, including arrests of military personnel suspected of plotting against the state.
          </p>
          </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
