          <strong>🇳🇱 Dutch spies warn about Russian cyberattacks </strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
The Dutch military intelligence agency (MIVD) has warned that Russia is intensifying <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-04-2025-h2-2-hybrid-warfare?source=website" target="_blank">hybrid warfare tactics</a> aimed at undermining democratic societies in Europe. In its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-26-04-2025-h2-3-2024-report?source=website" target="_blank">2024 report</a>, MIVD highlighted Russian cyberattacks targeting Dutch political party websites and public transport systems, timed to disrupt voter access ahead of the European elections. 
          </p>
          
